
// This Hyperlambda code updates the value of the [.token] node by concatenating the string "Bearer " with the current value of [.token]. It uses [set-value] to assign the new concatenated string, and [strings.concat] to perform the concatenation operation. The [get-value] slot retrieves the current value of [.token] to be concatenated.
set-value:x:@.token
   strings.concat
      .:"Bearer "
      get-value:x:@.token
